decks.notes: This deck focuses on very efficient removal and disruption spells to control the board and opponent's resources. It includes a wide range of targeted discard spells, board wipes, creature removal, and versatile removal cards like Swords to Plowshares and Path to Exile. The commander, Queen Marchesa, adds an extra layer of control with her Monarch ability, providing card advantage while also incentivizing opponents to attack each other instead of the player. The deck also includes card draw spells, mana acceleration, and powerful planeswalkers to help maintain control of the game. Overall, the key strategy is to disrupt the opponent's game plan, control the board, and outvalue them with efficient removal and card advantage.

This deck revolves around utilizing counterspells, removal spells, and evasion to control the game and protect Geist of Saint Traft, the commander. The goal is to disrupt the opponent's game plan while efficiently deploying threats and generating card advantage. The deck includes a wide range of counterspells like Force of Will and Cryptic Command, removal spells such as Swords to Plowshares and Council's Judgment, as well as efficient creatures like True-Name Nemesis and Snapcaster Mage. By leveraging Geist of Saint Traft's ability to create evasive Angel tokens and equipping powerful equipment like Sword of Fire and Ice, the deck aims to secure victory through a combination of control and aggression.

The focus of this deck is to quickly ramp up mana through various land cards and mana dorks to play powerful green creatures and overwhelm the opponent with aggressive plays. The commander, Titania, Protector of Argoth, synergizes with sacrificing lands and creating multiple 5/3 Elemental tokens, providing a constant stream of threats. Additional utility cards such as Garruk Wildspeaker, Birthing Pod, and Crucible of Worlds enhance the deck's versatility and resilience. The goal is to establish a strong board presence early on and maintain pressure throughout the game, utilizing the deck's ramp and card advantage to stay ahead of the opponent and secure a victory through overwhelming force.

This deck focuses on a tempo-based aggressive strategy, utilizing the combination of Vial Smasher the Fierce and Kraum, Ludevic's Opus as commanders to apply pressure and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck includes a versatile mix of counterspells, removal spells, and card draw to control the board and maintain tempo advantage. With a wide range of instant-speed interaction and powerful threats like True-Name Nemesis and Goblin Dark-Dwellers, the deck aims to efficiently deal with threats while presenting a clock for the opponent to answer. The mana base is optimized to support the deck's color requirements and ensure consistent access to different mana sources. Overall, the deck's strength lies in its ability to adapt to various situations and apply relentless pressure on the opponent.

This deck focuses on utilizing the powerful combination of Kraum, Ludevic's Opus and Vial Smasher the Fierce as commanders to create a fast-paced, aggressive strategy. The deck includes an array of efficient removal spells, counter magic, and card draw to control the board while dealing damage to the opponent. The inclusion of versatile spells like Demonic Tutor, Fact or Fiction, and Cryptic Command allows for flexibility in different situations. The mana base is optimized to support the deck's three-color identity, with access to key dual lands and fetch lands. By combining aggression with control elements, this deck aims to disrupt the opponent's strategy while dealing consistent damage to secure a win in the Duel Commander format.

This deck focuses on aggressive gameplay, utilizing Saskia the Unyielding as the commander to deal maximum damage quickly to the opponent. The deck includes a wide range of aggressive creatures such as Tarmogoyf, Siege Rhino, and Voice of Resurgence, as well as efficient removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Swords to Plowshares to clear the way for attacks. The mana base is optimized for quick and consistent access to all the necessary colors, ensuring a smooth curve of threats and answers. With a mix of creatures and spells aimed at applying pressure and disrupting the opponent's game plan, this deck aims to overwhelm and outpace the opposition in a fast-paced 1 vs 1 Duel Commander format.

The deck revolves around utilizing ramp cards and mana dorks to quickly accelerate mana production, allowing for early and powerful plays. The focus is on generating a large amount of mana to cast big threats like Primeval Titan and Craterhoof Behemoth to overwhelm the opponent. The deck also utilizes land-based strategies, such as sacrificing lands for value with cards like Zuran Orb and Crucible of Worlds, while also running utility lands like Wasteland and Tectonic Edge for disruption. The commander, Titania, Protector of Argoth, synergizes well with the deck's land theme, creating tokens and providing additional value when lands are sacrificed. Overall, the deck aims to be aggressive and proactive, taking advantage of its ramp and land synergies to overpower opponents quickly.
